That’s why nearly 100% of reviewers use these types of systems.
The service and application providers for accident assessment and repair collect the information they receive from the manufacturers to process it thereafter and offer it to their customers in the form of a useful program.
In Spain, Audatex, part of the American group Solera, is the market leader; 80% of all reviews are made with their products.
The other two companies competing in the tool market for reviewing and drafting a report are GtMotive and Eurotax.
Working with the data that the manufacturers provide is anything but simple.
According to Eduardo Velázquez, Sales Manager of Audatex, 63 manufacturers and importers are cooperating, each of them providing the information in a different format.
In addition, the amount of data to be processed is becoming ever larger, to the point that in the last five years more versions, variants and motorizations have come to the market than in the entire fifteen years before.
As soon as a new car comes on the market, work begins for the companies.
It is an arduous task, because each of the over a thousand vehicle parts must be cataloged and its price entered.
In addition, each model creates an "intelligent" graphic image, on which you can "click" different parts of the vehicle.
If this is a highly sold model, the work can be completed in a week if the procedure proceeds quickly.
If it is a less common car, it can take up to three or four months. Currently, Audatex has full information for 99.2% of cars sold in Spain.
Among the more exclusive models, for example, they have information about the Porsche models, but not about Ferrari or Lamborghini.
In terms of the fleet of vehicles driving on the roads, it is over 99%.
Audatex has eight centres worldwide (Spain, France, Germany, USA, Brazil, Mexico, China and Japan) that specialize in specific brands for the purpose of documenting and producing databases.
The national headquarters is located in Alcobendas (Madrid).
